# Catalog item images (unified resolver)

Use **one resolver** for every catalog row thumbnail so Equipment, Serialized Tools, Small Tools, Inventory, and Pricing Guide stay consistent.

## Entry point (`app/services/catalog_images.py`)

| Function | Use |
|----------|-----|
| `get_catalog_image_url(record, kind=...)` | Resolve browser URL or `None` |
| `catalog_thumbnail_html(record, kind=...)` | HTML `<img>` or placeholder |
| `render_catalog_thumbnail(record)` | Streamlit thumbnail |
| `build_catalog_image_context(assets_by_id=...)` | Name/asset lookups for small tools |

Pass explicit `kind` when known: `"asset"`, `"small_tool"`, `"inventory"`, `"pricing_guide"`.

**Do not** read `image_url` / `photo_url` directly in table UI code.

## Domain delegation

| Kind | Resolver |
|------|----------|
| `asset` / `equipment` / `serialized` | `get_asset_thumbnail_url` (+ linked catalog inherit) |
| `small_tool` | source asset → inventory name → pricing name → asset name |
| `inventory` | `get_inventory_image_url` (item → linked PG) |
| `pricing_guide` | `get_pricing_guide_image_url` (row → linked inventory/asset) |

Placeholders: inventory → 📦; assets / small tools → —

## Where to use

- Assets Equipment / Serialized Tools tables → `catalog_thumbnail_html(..., kind="asset")`
- Assets Small Tools tab → `catalog_thumbnail_html(..., kind="small_tool", context=ctx)`
- Inventory list/scan → existing `inventory_thumbnail_html` (wraps same inventory resolver)
- Job materials → `catalog_thumbnail_html` for inventory and pricing rows

## Do not

- Duplicate per-table image fallback chains
- Add new resolvers in page files — extend `catalog_images.py` or domain modules (`inventory_images.py`, etc.)
